"      </font>",
"      Maximum recommended dose of citalopram is 20 mg for patients &gt;60 years of age, with significant hepatic insufficiency, or taking interacting medications that can increase citalopram levels. Refer to topics on unipolar depression&nbsp;for more information.&nbsp;Specific interactions of citalopram with other medications may be determined using the drug interactions tool (Lexi-Interact Online) included in UpToDate. This tool can be accessed from the UpToDate online search page or through the individual drug information topics in the section on Drug interactions.",
